<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.193248>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 4. Habitus of 1) Antiporus bakewellii (male), 2) A. kalbarriensis sp. n. (male) (scale bar 1 mm). Lateral (a) and ventral views (b) of median lobes of aedeagi of 3) A. bakewellii and 4) A. kalbarriensis sp. n. (scale bar 0.4 mm). Photos: L. Hendrich." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/193248/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.193249>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Right male proclaw of Antiporus kalbarriensis sp. n. (scale bar 0.1 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/193249/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.193250>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Map showing the two collecting localities of A. kalbarriensis sp. n. (black dots) in Western Australia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/193250/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.193251>
    dc:description "FIGURES 7 – 8. Habitat of A. kalbarriensis sp. n., 7) View over the Murchison River from Hawk´s Head Lookout; 8) Backwater pool at Murchison River near Ross Graham Lookout (Loc. 19 / 183). Photos: L. Hendrich." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/193251/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

